From: Yang Yingliang <yangyingliang@huawei.com>
Date: Fri, 22 Apr 2022 11:28:54 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] drm/rockchip: vop: fix possible null-ptr-deref in vop_bind()
Git-commit: f8c242908ad15bbd604d3bcb54961b7d454c43f8
Patch-mainline: v5.19-rc1
References: CVE-2022-49491 bsc#1238539

It will cause null-ptr-deref in resource_size(), if platform_get_resource()
returns NULL, move calling resource_size() after devm_ioremap_resource() that
will check 'res' to avoid null-ptr-deref.

Fixes: 2048e3286f34 ("drm: rockchip: Add basic drm driver")
Signed-off-by: Yang Yingliang <yangyingliang@huawei.com>
Signed-off-by: Heiko Stuebner <heiko@sntech.de>
Link: https://patchwork.freedesktop.org/patch/msgid/20220422032854.2995175-1-yangyingliang@huawei.com
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/rockchip/rockchip_drm_vop.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/rockchip/rockchip_drm_vop.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/rockchip/rockchip_drm_vop.c
@@ -1627,10 +1627,10 @@ static int vop_bind(struct device *dev,
 	vop_win_init(vop);
 
 	res = platform_get_resource(pdev, IORESOURCE_MEM, 0);
-	vop->len = resource_size(res);
 	vop->regs = devm_ioremap_resource(dev, res);
 	if (IS_ERR(vop->regs))
 		return PTR_ERR(vop->regs);
+	vop->len = resource_size(res);
 
 	vop->regsbak = devm_kzalloc(dev, vop->len, GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (!vop->regsbak)
